    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-01-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-01-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="882"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d882">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890D.927/90</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kelley</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="6" xml:id="d882fn6">Ambassador MacMurray resumed charge of
                        the Embassy on this date.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 342</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-01-18">January 18,
                            1939</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Secretary of State transmits herewith copies of telegrams<note n="6a"
                        xml:id="d882fn6a">The four telegrams printed <hi rend="italic"
                        >supra</hi>.</note> exchanged between the Department and the American Consul
                    General at Beirut, and between the Department and the American Embassy at <pb
                        facs="0841" n="835" xml:id="pg_835"/> Paris, regarding certain apprehensions
                    felt by the Committee for the Excavation of Antioch and its Vicinity lest its
                    contract for excavation work in that area be abrogated by the local authorities
                    in the Hatay.</p>
                <p>While the Department does not desire the Embassy to undertake any discussions at
                    the present time with the Turkish authorities regarding American interests in
                    the Hatay, it requests the Embassy to submit observations regarding the
                    appropriateness and probable effectiveness of representations which might be
                    made direct to the Turkish Government regarding matters relating to the
                    Hatay.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
